broadwood stadium, also referred to as simply broadwood, is a multi-use community stadium and sports complex situated in cumbernauld, north lanarkshire, scotland. the stadium was opened in 1994 and since then has been the home venue of clyde f.c., cumbernauld colts f.c. and the home of bt sport scottish rugby academy, glasgow and the west since 2015. it has staged the final of scottish footballs' scottish challenge cup on four occasions and scottish rugbys' rbs finals day. the stadium has also held international rugby league